    elif operation == '*' :

            return result

Suppose your 9-year old daughter and your 6-year old son are playing a board game together, and she tells you, "There was a tie and we had to take turns to choose which side of the board got its turn to be on".

The question that you could ask yourself should therefore be: "What is the probability of this board game being a tie?"

This is often referred to as "asking the wrong question", and is one of the easiest ways to trip an interviewer up. By asking about the game itself and what options you have, you could also be misled to picking, e.g. "the 6-year old gets his turn, because he's younger". This may seem a logical choice, but what if the child playing the board game is the 6-year old!?
